# FlyRank Capstone — Development Rules

## Tech Stack
- Frontend: React / Next.js
- Styling: Tailwind CSS
- Language: TypeScript

## Code Style & Conventions
- Use clean, modular, functional components — no class components.
- Prioritize semantic HTML and accessible UI design.
- Keep components small and single-purpose.
- Follow Conventional Commits for all repository updates.
- Component files use PascalCase (e.g., `UserCard.tsx`).
- Use hooks for state management.

## Folder Structure
- `app/` — routes, layouts, and route-local components (Next.js App Router)
- `components/` — shared, reusable UI components
- `lib/` — shared types, utilities, and hooks

## Notes for AI Assistant
- This project is early-stage — ask clarifying questions before assuming architecture or features.
- Explain reasoning before making changes.
- Prioritize maintainability over cleverness.